article.linkText: Rai scores 20 to carry Dartmouth over Columbia 76-63
article.story: NEW YORK -- — Aaryn Rai had 20 points as Dartmouth ended its seven-game road losing streak, topping Columbia 76-63 on Saturday. Brendan Barry had 13 points for Dartmouth (5-12, 2-4 Ivy League). Dame Adelekun added 12 points. Garrison Wade had 11 points. Liam Murphy had 17 points for the Lions (4-14, 1-5), whose losing streak stretched to four games. Ike Nweke added 15 points and seven rebounds. Patrick Harding had 12 points and seven rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
